-- Gulbis Defeats Garcia-Lopez in St. Petersburg Open Tennis Final
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-09-22T15:35:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-22/radwanska-defeats-pavlyuchenkova-to-win-tennis-s-korea-open.html
Latvia’s Ernests Gulbis recovered
to beat Guillermo Garcia-Lopez of Spain in the final of tennis’s
St. Petersburg Open.  No. 6 seed Gulbis defeated the unseeded Spaniard 3-6, 6-4,
6-0 after winning the last 11 games. It was Gulbis’s fourth ATP
title.  Second-seed Gilles Simon beat French countryman and No. 1
seed Jo-Wilfried Tsonga 6-4, 6-3 in the final of the Moselle
Open in Metz,  France . It was Simon’s first ATP title for 17
months.  Top seed Agnieszka Radwanska of  Poland  fought back to
defeat Russia’s Anastasia Pavlyuchenkova in three sets to win
the Korea Open.  Radwanska beat the No. 3 seed 6-7 (6-8), 6-3, 6-4 in Seoul
for her third title of the year and the first since January.  “It was a very close match, tight sets all of them, but I
was just a little bit better in the important moments,” world
No. 4 Radwanska said on the  WTA website .  Chinese wildcard Zhang Shuai beat Vania King of the U.S. 7-6 (7-1), 6-1 in the final of the Guangzhou International to win
her first WTA title.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 